<emphasis id="B915EAECC45D7C3ADAB0F841BA18F812" bold="true" box="[136,261,2009,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
General habitus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D7DC45D7C3ADBE9F841B8A1F812" authority="Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai" authorityName="Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[465,956,2009,2034]" class="Insecta" family="Endomychidae" genus="Rhomeocalpsua" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torosa" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45D7C3ADBE9F841B9A6F812" box="[465,699,2009,2033]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Rhomeocalpsua torosa</emphasis>
Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45D7C3AD9FFF842BF75F811" bold="true" box="[967,1128,2010,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2265797C45D7C3AD9FFF842BF75F811" box="[967,1128,2010,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype, NIGP180054, under widefield fluorescence. 
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45D7C3ADB43F865BA90F7F6" bold="true" box="[379,397,2045,2069]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">A</emphasis>
, Dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45D7C3AD818F866B92CF7F5" bold="true" box="[544,561,2046,2070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">B</emphasis>
, Ventral view. Scale bars = 500 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF1E6676C45C7C3BDAB0FB1DB891FB21" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530511" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6530511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530511/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149" startId="3.[136,235,1157,1181]" targetBox="[215,1372,189,1134]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BDE36FEC45C7C3BDAB0FB1DB891FB21" blockId="3.[136,1452,1157,1218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45C7C3BDAB0FB1DBA18FB7E" bold="true" box="[136,261,1157,1181]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
General habitus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D7DC45C7C3BDBE9FB1EB8A1FB7D" authority="Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai" authorityName="Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[465,956,1158,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Endomychidae" genus="Rhomeocalpsua" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torosa" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45C7C3BDBE9FB1EB9A6FB7E" box="[465,699,1158,1182]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Rhomeocalpsua torosa</emphasis>
Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45C7C3BD9FFFB1EBF75FB7D" bold="true" box="[967,1128,1158,1182]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2265797C45C7C3BD9FFFB1EBF75FB7D" box="[967,1128,1158,1182]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. 
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45C7C3BDB5FFB31BA64FB22" bold="true" box="[359,377,1193,1217]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">A</emphasis>
, Dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B915EAECC45C7C3BD834FB32B900FB21" bold="true" box="[524,541,1194,1218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">B</emphasis>
, Ventral view. Scale bars = 500 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDE36FEC45C7C3BDA85F9B1BAB6F91D" blockId="3.[136,778,1277,1902]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
Legs relatively long and slender. Trochanterofemoral joint oblique. Femora with deep and long groove (nearly throughout their length) for receiving tibiae (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45C7C3BD8BEF9EBB9E0F96D" box="[646,765,1651,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1533,1557]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Details of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, dorsal view. B, Head, ventral view. C, Antenna, dorsal view. D, Antenna, ventral view. E, Mesothorax, ventral view. F, Abdominal base, ventral view. G, Abdominal apex, ventral view. H, Mesotarsus, ventral view. I, Metatarsus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–9, antennomeres 1–9; cl, clypeus; lbp, labial palp; msc, mesocoxa; msf, mesofemur; mst1–3, mesotarsomeres 1–3; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mtt1–3, metatarsomeres 1–3; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; v1–6, ventrites 1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530513/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Fig. 4E, F</figureCitation>
). Tibiae without apical spurs, with short spines surrounding apex (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45C7C3BDAF6F926BA36F93B" box="[206,299,1726,1752]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1533,1557]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Details of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, dorsal view. B, Head, ventral view. C, Antenna, dorsal view. D, Antenna, ventral view. E, Mesothorax, ventral view. F, Abdominal base, ventral view. G, Abdominal apex, ventral view. H, Mesotarsus, ventral view. I, Metatarsus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–9, antennomeres 1–9; cl, clypeus; lbp, labial palp; msc, mesocoxa; msf, mesofemur; mst1–3, mesotarsomeres 1–3; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mtt1–3, metatarsomeres 1–3; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; v1–6, ventrites 1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530513/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
). Tarsi 3-3-3; tarsomeres simple (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45C7C3BD892F926BB8EF91D" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1533,1557]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Details of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, dorsal view. B, Head, ventral view. C, Antenna, dorsal view. D, Antenna, ventral view. E, Mesothorax, ventral view. F, Abdominal base, ventral view. G, Abdominal apex, ventral view. H, Mesotarsus, ventral view. I, Metatarsus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–9, antennomeres 1–9; cl, clypeus; lbp, labial palp; msc, mesocoxa; msf, mesofemur; mst1–3, mesotarsomeres 1–3; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mtt1–3, metatarsomeres 1–3; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; v1–6, ventrites 1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530513/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Fig. 4H, I</figureCitation>
). Pretarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDE36FEC45C7C3BDA85F891BA2AF88D" blockId="3.[136,778,1277,1902]" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="135A2A7BC45C7C3BDB79F891BAA2F8C0" box="[321,447,1801,1827]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,235,1533,1557]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetId="figure-132@4.[145,1443,198,1509]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Details of Rhomeocalpsua torosa Li, Tomaszewska &amp; Cai, gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180054, under confocal microscopy. A, Head, dorsal view. B, Head, ventral view. C, Antenna, dorsal view. D, Antenna, ventral view. E, Mesothorax, ventral view. F, Abdominal base, ventral view. G, Abdominal apex, ventral view. H, Mesotarsus, ventral view. I, Metatarsus, dorsal view. Abbreviations: a1–9, antennomeres 1–9; cl, clypeus; lbp, labial palp; msc, mesocoxa; msf, mesofemur; mst1–3, mesotarsomeres 1–3; msv, mesoventrite; mtf, metafemur; mtt1–3, metatarsomeres 1–3; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; v1–6, ventrites 1–6. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530513/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="149">Fig. 4F, G</figureCitation>
) with six ventrites; ventrite 1 slightly longer than ventrite 2–4 combined, without postcoxal lines.
</paragraph>
